
[1]gesticulation

   GESTICULA'TION, n. [L. gesticulatio.]

   1. The act of making gestures, to express passion or enforce
   sentiments.

   2. Gesture; a motion of the body or limbs in speaking, or in
   representing action or passion, and enforcing arguments and sentiments.

   3. Antic tricks or motions.
